diff:1620354457:1619999162:=47,61c47%0a%3c #foxbegin 210507-022737-575600#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Facial Expressions %0a%3c -> - AlexanderW%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c Though not phonology, facial expressions are extremely important in conveying the meaning and intent behind the signed sentences and questions.%0a%3c %0a%3c In any sign language, facial expressions do 2 major things. First, in most languages, an eyebrow raise denotes a question mark. Secondly, facial expressions are used to express emotion - sort of like how, when we speak, we emphasize and speed/slow down certain words, or we use the quality of speech to denote sarcasm.%0a%3c %0a%3c As the study referenced in this expansion mentions, when combining questions with different emotions, the facial expressions get combined, and thus get quite complex. The reason why this study is so important is in computer translation. As facial expressions can vary only a little bit and mean vastly different things, a computer has to be extraordinarily accurate in detecting minute changes in body and head position, eyebrow position, and how the signing and face interact.%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.uib.no/en/hf/136874/complex-system-facial-expressions-sign-language#:~:text=%2522In%2520sign%2520language%252C%2520facial%2520expressions,or%2520when%2520quoting%2520someone%2520else.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210507-022737-575600#%0a---%0a> %0a
